TestCase_GC_000304_TestSeekObjectData (  )
Trusted Applications dependencies:
5d911d63250450feba1a998cedfd8ab2
Pre Conditions:
none
Focus:
TEE_SeekObjectData() works correctly
Test Steps:
1) create a persistent object using TEE_CreatePersistentObject()
2) close the object using TEE_CloseObject()
3) open the object using TEE_OpenPersistentObject() with TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_READ | TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_WRITE_META
4) seek the position at the beginning of the file using TEE_SeekObjectData()
with offset=0 and whence=TEE_DATA_SEEK_SET
5) read the data (from this position) using TEE_ReadObjectData()
6) compare the the data to the one that is expected
7) seek the position in the middle of the file using TEE_SeekObjectData()
with offset=some offset and whence=TEE_DATA_SEEK_SET
8) read the data (from this position) using TEE_ReadObjectData()
9) compare the the data to the one that is expected
Verification:
Data read after TEE_SeekObjectData() is the one that expected
Post Conditions:
TEEC_SUCCESS

TestCase_GC_000307_TestWriteObjectData_2 (  )
Trusted Applications dependencies:
5d911d63250450feba1a998cedfd8ab2
Pre Conditions:
none
Focus:
TEE_WriteObjectData(), TEE_SeekObjectData(), TEE_ReadObjectData() works correctly
Test Steps:
1) create a persistent object with some inital data using TEE_CreatePersistentObject()
2) close the object using TEE_CloseObject()
3) open the object using TEE_OpenPersistentObject() with TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_WRITE
4) write first piece of data using TEE_WriteObjectData() so overwriting the initial content
5) close the object using TEE_CloseObject()
6) open the object using TEE_OpenPersistentObject() with TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_READ|TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_WRITE
7) read the data using TEE_ReadObjectData()
8) check the length and the content of the data read
9) write second piece of data using TEE_WriteObjectData() to the end of the first data
10) close the object using TEE_CloseObject()
11) open the object using TEE_OpenPersistentObject()
with TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_READ
12) read the data using TEE_ReadObjectData() by two chunks
13) check the length and the content of the data read
14) close the object using TEE_CloseObject()
15) open the object using TEE_OpenPersistentObject()
with TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_WRITE
16) set the data position indicator few bytes
beyond the end of the object using TEE_SeekObjectData()
17) write third piece of data using TEE_WriteObjectData() to this position
18) close the object using TEE_CloseObject()
19) open the object using TEE_OpenPersistentObject()
with TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_READ|TEE_DATA_FLAG_ACCESS_WRITE
20) read the data using TEE_ReadObjectData() by two chunks
21) check the length and the content of the data read
22) set the data position indicator the same few bytes
beyond the second chunk using TEE_SeekObjectData()
23) read the third piece of data using TEE_ReadObjectData()
24) check the length and the content of the data read
Verification:
The length and the content of the data read match the expected ones
Post Conditions:
TEE_SUCCESS
Manual Execution:

Focus:
TEST CRYPTO With DataStorage
Test Steps:
TEST CRYPTO With DataStorage
verify decrypt and encrypt from persistent object for TEE_TYPE_RSA_KEYPAIR
Test Steps:
1/ TEE_InitRefAttribute for 8 needed attribute for TEE_TYPE_RSA_KEYPAIR
2/ TEE_AllocateTransientObject TEE_TYPE_RSA_KEYPAIR, hTransiObj
3/ TEE_PopulateTransientObject with 8 Initialized attributes
4/ TEE_CreatePersistentObject, hPersistObj, with This transient, hTransiObj
5/ TEE_CloseObject hPersistObj
6/ TEE_FreeTransientObject hTransiObj
7/ TEE_OpenPersistentObject hPersistObj
8/ TEE_AllocateOperation,operationHandleEncrypt, for TEE_ALG_RSAES_PKCS1_V1_5 algorithm
9/ TEE_SetOperationKey,operationHandleEncrypt, with hPersistObj
10/ TEE_AsymmetricEncrypt operationHandleEncrypt,from PlainTexData; pCipher,&nCipherLen are the outputs
11/ TEE_FreeOperation(operationHandleEncrypt)
12/ TEE_AllocateOperation , operationHandleDecrypt, for TEE_ALG_RSAES_PKCS1_V1_5 algo
13/ TEE_SetOperationKey(operationHandleDecrypt,hPersistObj)
14/ TEE_AsymmetricDecrypt, operationHandleDecrypt,pCipher,&nCipherLen, pData, &nDataLen are the output
15/ TEE_MemCompare PlainTexData with pData
Verification:
Encrypt with Private key and decrypt with public key will give same Palin text
